<subSubSection pageId="13" pageNumber="14" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="13.[151,1437,937,2008]" pageId="13" pageNumber="14">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,322,1153,1179]" pageId="13" pageNumber="14">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
This species belongs to the group of dark 
<taxonomicName box="[808,971,1153,1179]" pageId="13" pageNumber="14">
<emphasis box="[808,881,1154,1179]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="14">Druon</emphasis>
species
</taxonomicName>
(also comprising 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Cuesta-Porta &amp; Melika &amp; Nicholls &amp; Stone &amp; Pujade-Villar" authorityYear="2022" box="[1176,1295,1154,1179]" class="Insecta" family="Cynipidae" genus="Druon" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="13" pageNumber="14" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="gregori">
<emphasis box="[1176,1295,1154,1179]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="14">D. gregori</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Cuesta-Porta &amp; Melika &amp; Nicholls &amp; Stone &amp; Pujade-Villar" authorityYear="2022" box="[1310,1437,1154,1179]" class="Insecta" family="Cynipidae" genus="Druon" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="13" pageNumber="14" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="serretae">
<emphasis box="[1310,1437,1154,1179]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="14">D. serretae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Cuesta-Porta &amp; Melika &amp; Nicholls &amp; Stone &amp; Pujade-Villar" authorityYear="2022" box="[197,337,1189,1215]" class="Insecta" family="Cynipidae" genus="Druon" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="13" pageNumber="14" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="alexandri">
<emphasis box="[197,337,1189,1215]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="14">D. alexandri</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
). Differs from 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Cuesta-Porta &amp; Melika &amp; Nicholls &amp; Stone &amp; Pujade-Villar" authorityYear="2022" box="[504,620,1190,1215]" class="Insecta" family="Cynipidae" genus="Druon" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="13" pageNumber="14" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="gregori">
<emphasis box="[504,620,1190,1215]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="14">D. gregori</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in having small ocelli, OOL 1.3× as long as the diameter of lateral ocellus (OOL as long as the diameter of lateral ocellus in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Cuesta-Porta &amp; Melika &amp; Nicholls &amp; Stone &amp; Pujade-Villar" authorityYear="2022" box="[708,825,1226,1251]" class="Insecta" family="Cynipidae" genus="Druon" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="13" pageNumber="14" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="gregori">
<emphasis box="[708,825,1226,1251]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="14">D. gregori</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<figureCitation box="[840,924,1225,1251]" captionStart="FIGURES 46–49" captionStartId="23.[151,264,1758,1782]" captionTargetBox="[183,1395,934,1722]" captionTargetId="figure-309@23.[173,1414,921,1734]" captionTargetPageId="23" captionText="FIGURES 46–49. Druon gregori, sp. nov., asexual female. 46–48, head: 46, frontal view, 47, dorsal view, 48, posterior view. 49, antenna." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6520498" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6520498/files/figure.png" pageId="13" pageNumber="14">Fig. 47</figureCitation>
)). Differs from 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Cuesta-Porta &amp; Melika &amp; Nicholls &amp; Stone &amp; Pujade-Villar" authorityYear="2022" box="[1100,1225,1226,1251]" class="Insecta" family="Cynipidae" genus="Druon" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="13" pageNumber="14" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="serretae">
<emphasis box="[1100,1225,1226,1251]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="14">D. serretae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in the shape of the head and having the notaulus incomplete (
<figureCitation box="[627,709,1261,1287]" captionStart="FIGURES 16–19" captionStartId="15.[151,264,1258,1282]" captionTargetBox="[161,1416,273,1234]" captionTargetId="figure-58@15.[160,1427,273,1234]" captionTargetPageId="15" captionText="FIGURES 16–19. Druon flocculentum, comb. nov., asexual female. 16, head, frontal view. 17, head, mesosoma, metasoma, lateral view. 18, head and mesoscutum, dorsal view. 19, mesoscutellum and propodeum, dorsal view. Photos were taken by M. Buffington." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6520481" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6520481/files/figure.png" pageId="13" pageNumber="14">Fig. 18</figureCitation>
) (complete in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Cuesta-Porta &amp; Melika &amp; Nicholls &amp; Stone &amp; Pujade-Villar" authorityYear="2022" box="[874,1000,1262,1287]" class="Insecta" family="Cynipidae" genus="Druon" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="13" pageNumber="14" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="serretae">
<emphasis box="[874,1000,1262,1287]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="14">D. serretae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<figureCitation box="[1015,1113,1261,1287]" captionStart="FIGURES 228–231" captionStartId="72.[151,264,1813,1837]" captionTargetBox="[159,1419,431,1777]" captionTargetId="figure-152@72.[154,1434,417,1789]" captionTargetPageId="72" captionText="FIGURES 228–231. Druon serretae, sp. nov., asexual female. 228, mesosoma, lateral view. 229–230, mesoscutum and mesoscutellum dorsal view. 231, metascutellum and propodeum, posterodorsal view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6520641" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6520641/files/figure.png" pageId="13" pageNumber="14">Fig. 229</figureCitation>
)). It resembles 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Cuesta-Porta &amp; Melika &amp; Nicholls &amp; Stone &amp; Pujade-Villar" authorityYear="2022" box="[1287,1429,1261,1287]" class="Insecta" family="Cynipidae" genus="Druon" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="13" pageNumber="14" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="alexandri">
<emphasis box="[1287,1429,1261,1287]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="14">D. alexandri</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, but 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Cuesta-Porta &amp; Melika &amp; Nicholls &amp; Stone &amp; Pujade-Villar" authorityYear="2022" baseAuthorityName="Lyon" baseAuthorityYear="1996" box="[193,370,1297,1323]" class="Insecta" family="Cynipidae" genus="Druon" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="13" pageNumber="14" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="flocculentum">
<emphasis box="[193,370,1297,1323]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="14">D. flocculentum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
presents with a transfacial distance shorter than height of eye (
